cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a time-division uplink transmission scheme and analyzes its spectral efficiency and outage performance, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed scheme involves device-to-device (D2D) and infrastructure cooperation, which are important topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper formulates common and individual outage probabilities, which can be considered as a system-level analysis. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed scheme can potentially improve the performance of multimedia applications in cellular networks. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves mathematical modeling and analysis of the proposed scheme, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem.
